"""
rr2_nmf_gui_ver4_1_full.py

Residual-aware / residual-redistributed recursive NMF GUI for EELS/EDS spectral-imaging data.

Features
--------
1. Data loading
   - .npy / .npz
   - .bcf / .dm3 / .dm4 / .emd / .hspy / .h5 / .hdf5 / .msa via HyperSpy/RosettaSciIO if installed

2. ROI before processing
   - Spatial ROI: Y start/end, X start/end
   - Channel ROI: channel start/end
   - Energy ROI: energy start/end, automatically mapped to nearest channel index

3. Analysis
   - Conventional NMF
   - Recursive rank-k NMF
   - Residual handling modes:
       discard
       redistribute_equal: X_child_i = W_i H_i + (X - W H) / rank
       explicit_branch

4. Quantification
   - Component energy without constructing full outer matrices
   - Residual energy and residual summaries calculated chunk-wise
   - Node/global energy ratios
   - Conventional NMF W/H correlation matrices

5. Visualization
   - Raw Data: XY image = sum over spectrum, spectrum = sum over space
   - rr-NMF Tree: wrapped layout. Component image above spectrum. Residual image/spectrum below components.
   - Conventional NMF: W image + H spectrum, plus final residual image/spectrum
   - Energy Summary
   - Colorbar without text labels
   - No scale-bar white boxes
   - No spectrum Y-axis titles
   - Explicit Zoom + / Zoom - / Fit Width / Reset / pan buttons

Install
-------
pip install numpy pandas scipy scikit-learn matplotlib PyQt5

Optional microscopy loaders
---------------------------
pip install hyperspy exspy rosettasciio
"""

